subSection.paragraph:
The flounder genus 

Pseudorhombus
Bleeker, 1862

(
Paralichthyidae
) includes medium to large sized demersal fishes, distributed off the continental coast and coastal islands in the Indo-West Pacific and eastern Pacific Ocean (
Norman 1934
; 
Amaoka and Hensley 2001
). Twenty-five valid species have been recognized worldwide (
Amaoka and Hensley 2001
; 
Hensley and Amaoka 2022
; 
Fricke et al. 2023
), the following seven having been recorded from 
Japan
(see 
Nakabo 2002
; 
Nakabo and Doiuchi 2013
; 
Amaoka 2016
): 

P. arsius
(Hamilton, 1822)

; 

P. cinnamoneus
(Temminck and Schlegel, 1846)

; 

P. dupliciocellatus
Regan, 1905

; 

P. levisquamis
(Oshima, 1927)

; 

P. oligodon
(Bleeker, 1854)

; 

P. oculocirris
Amaoka, 1969

; and 

P. pentophthalmus
Günther, 1862

.

